{
  "name": "RPlog_The_Price_Of_Tea",
  "title": "The Price of Tea",
  "summary": "On Tatooine, the Sith apprentice Dareus intercepts the newly arrived Dr. Lynae Cassius -- who travels under the alias Laenira -- and steers her into Chalmun's Cantina for a volatile confrontation over whether she betrayed Sith secrets to the New Republic. The mercenary Axel Vichten arrives spoiling for blood, and the table erupts into threats and drawn weapons as Lynae insists she revealed nothing of Cochran or the base. A would-be philosopher named Atton needles Dareus about being a mere errand boy, nearly getting shot, while the timid Draga emissary Ariana Seri talks her way into the dangerous gathering. The arena shifts when Darth Malign himself glides in with an entourage of inhuman guards, Force-hurling Dareus into a wall and declaring everyone present his prisoners, to be measured for usefulness aboard the Predator. Lynae lashes out with a forbidden kick and Malign drains her with a Force Vampire touch. In a quieter coda aboard her ship Red Sky, Malign delivers the promised vial of Dareus's blood, presses Lynae about her experiments and the Sith disease she studies, and warns that the blood of the Sith is poison to the soul before vanishing into the shadows.",
